result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler P Ziehme was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tyler P Ziehme in court with attorney Andrew Joseph Harrington.  John Michael O'Boyle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
THIS COVERS 15CM439, 16CM46, 15CT174, 16CM150, 15TR622, 15TR623, 15TR2183, 15TR2184. 
Argument by State. Argument by Defense. Defendant addresses the court. 

15CT174: Defendant pleads guilty to count 1. Court accepts the plea and finds the Defendant guilty. Count 2 is dimissed and read-in. 
Court relates and orders:
$1492.00 fine 
10 days jail with Huber and good time. 
14 month drivers license revocation 
14 month ignition interlock device
AODA and comply with recommended follow-up treatment. .171 BAC. 
Costs.

15CM439: Defendant pleads guilty. Court accepts the plea and finds the Defendant guilty. 
Court relates and orders: 10 days jail (consecutive to any sentence being served) with Huber. The jail time may be served by 80 hours of community service work to be completed within 120 days.   If the defendant fails to perform the community service as ordered he/she must report to the jail as ordered with credit of 1 day of jail served for each 8 hours of community service completed.
Costs. 

16CM46: State moves to amend count 1 to OWI 3rd (non aggravated). Court grants amendment. Defendant pleads guilty to count 1. Court accepts the plea and finds the Defendant guilty. Counts 2 and 3 are dismissed and read-in. 
Court relates and orders: 
$1744.00 fine 
60 days jail with Huber and good time consecutive to 15CT174
24 month drivers license revocation 
24 month ignition interlock device
AODA and comply with recommended follow-up treatment. .149 BAC. 
Costs. 

16CM150: Defendant pleads guilty. Court accepts the plea and finds the Defendant guilty. 
Court relates and orders: 
20 days jail with Huber and good time consecutive to 15CT174 and 16CM46. 
Costs. 

15TR622: Defendant pleads guilty. Court accepts the plea and finds the Defendant guilty and orders a $515.50 forfeiture with 60 days to pay or payment plan. 

15TR623, 15TR2183 and 15TR2184 - Dismissed and read-in. 
JAIL FAXED.   Order for DNA given to the defendant in court. Report to Barron County Jail by 3:00 PM today.

May not go onto any premises where alcohol is sold.
Must not operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.
Daily PBTs at the Barron County Sheriff's Dept.  at 6:00 a.m.

Defendant Tyler P Ziehme in court with attorney Andrew Joseph Harrington.  Angela Lynn Beranek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
